<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1513,2080]" lastBlockId="8.[136,1452,158,545]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1874,1900]" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">Notes:</emphasis>
According to the classification proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Consiglio, G. &amp; Setti, L." box="[779,1082,1873,1900]" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" refId="ref4971" refString="Consiglio, G. &amp; Setti, L. (2008) Il genere Crepidotus in Europa. Associazione Micologica Bresadola, Trento, Italy, 344 pp." type="book" year="2008">Consiglio and Setti (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Bau &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" box="[1096,1228,1873,1900]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ulmicola">
<emphasis box="[1096,1228,1873,1900]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">C. ulmicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be assigned to series 
<emphasis box="[247,389,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">Dochmiopus</emphasis>
Consiglio &amp; Setti, section 
<emphasis box="[720,862,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">Dochmiopus</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[881,1258,1909,1935]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Dochmiopus">
<emphasis box="[881,1004,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">Crepidotus</emphasis>
subgen. 
<emphasis box="[1116,1258,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">Dochmiopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The tiny white basidiomes, tomentose pileus, and weakly rugulose basidiospores are the most distinctive features for distinguishing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Bau &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,267,1981,2008]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ulmicola">
<emphasis box="[136,267,1981,2008]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">C. ulmicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other 
<taxonomicName box="[400,619,1981,2007]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[400,523,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">Crepidotus</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
Only a few 
<taxonomicName box="[758,970,1981,2007]" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis box="[758,881,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">Crepidotus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
produce a basidiome similar in size to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Bau &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" box="[169,302,2017,2044]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ulmicola">
<emphasis box="[169,302,2017,2044]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">C. ulmicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whose pileus is less than 
<quantity box="[612,693,2018,2044]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
in diameter. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hesler, L. R. &amp; Smith, A. H." box="[846,1111,2017,2044]" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" refId="ref7196" refString="Hesler, L. R. &amp; Smith, A. H. (1965) North American Species of Crepidotus. Hafner Publishing Company, New York, London, 168 pp." type="book" year="1965">Hesler &amp; Smith (1965)</bibRefCitation>
assigned most species with a pileus not exceeding 
<quantity box="[375,455,2054,2080]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
in diameter to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hesler &amp; A. H. Sm. sect. Sphaerula Hesler &amp; A. H. Sm." authorityName="Hesler &amp; A. H. Sm." class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="30" order="Agaricales" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="section" section="Sphaerula" subGenus="Sphaerula">
<emphasis box="[627,750,2053,2079]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">Crepidotus</emphasis>
subgen. 
<emphasis box="[852,967,2053,2079]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">Sphaerula</emphasis>
Hesler &amp; A.H. Sm. sect. 
<emphasis box="[1255,1370,2053,2079]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">Sphaerula</emphasis>
Hesler &amp; A.H. Sm.
</taxonomicName>
or subsect. 
<emphasis box="[414,538,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">Colorantes</emphasis>
Hesler &amp; A.H. Sm.; however, all such species are distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Bau &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" box="[1281,1414,158,185]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ulmicola">
<emphasis box="[1281,1414,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">C. ulmicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on account of the honey-yellow to brownish or pale tawny pileus. In subsect. 
<emphasis box="[996,1120,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">Colorantes</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ellis &amp; Everhart (1894: 322)" authorityName="Ellis &amp; Everhart" authorityPageNumber="322" authorityYear="1894" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="albidus">
<emphasis box="[1137,1254,194,221]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">C. albidus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ellis, J. B. &amp; Everhart, B. M." pageId="8" pageNumber="30" pagination="322 - 386" refId="ref6846" refString="Ellis, J. B. &amp; Everhart, B. M. (1894) New Species of Fungi from Various Localities. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 46: 322 - 386." type="journal article" year="1894">Ellis &amp; Everhart (1894: 322)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Murrill (1943: 430)" authorityName="Murrill" authorityPageNumber="430" authorityYear="1943" box="[322,666,230,257]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="amarus">
<emphasis box="[322,439,231,257]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">C. amarus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Murrill, W. A." box="[446,666,230,256]" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" pagination="422 - 433" refId="ref8410" refString="Murrill, W. A. (1943) Some Southern novelties. Mycologia 35: 422 - 433. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1943.12017497" type="journal article" year="1943">Murrill (1943: 430)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
have the greatest morphological resemblance to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Bau &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" box="[1215,1346,230,257]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ulmicola">
<emphasis box="[1215,1346,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">C. ulmicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but they differ in basidiospore size. 
<bibRefCitation author="Krisai-Greilhuber, I. &amp; Senn-Irlet, B. &amp; Voglmayr, H." box="[446,795,266,292]" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" pagination="515 - 539" refId="ref7732" refString="Krisai-Greilhuber, I., Senn-Irlet, B. &amp; Voglmayr, H. (2002) Notes on Crepidotus from Mexico and the South-Eastern USA. Persoonia 17: 515 - 539. https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1439 - 0507.2002.00742. x" type="journal article" year="2002">
Krisai-Greilhuber 
<emphasis box="[654,712,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
(2002)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ellis &amp; Everhart" authorityYear="1894" box="[919,1035,266,293]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="albidus">
<emphasis box="[919,1035,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">C. albidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as possessing 5.9–6.9 × 4.7–5.6 μm basidiospores and occasionally clamps. The basidiospores of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ellis &amp; Everhart" authorityYear="1894" box="[814,928,302,329]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="albidus">
<emphasis box="[814,928,302,329]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">C. albidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinctly shorter than those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Bau &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" box="[1315,1444,302,329]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ulmicola">
<emphasis box="[1315,1444,302,329]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">C. ulmicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murrill" authorityYear="1943" box="[136,351,338,364]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="amarus">
<emphasis box="[136,351,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">Crepidotus amarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Bau &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" box="[501,632,338,365]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ulmicola">
<emphasis box="[501,632,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">C. ulmicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in possessing clavate to cylindrical cheilocystidia, which are lageniform in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hesler &amp; Smith 1965)" baseAuthorityName="Hesler &amp; Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[165,563,374,401]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ulmicola">
<emphasis box="[165,296,374,401]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">C. ulmicola</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hesler, L. R. &amp; Smith, A. H." box="[310,555,374,401]" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" refId="ref7196" refString="Hesler, L. R. &amp; Smith, A. H. (1965) North American Species of Crepidotus. Hafner Publishing Company, New York, London, 168 pp." type="book" year="1965">Hesler &amp; Smith 1965</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">
In our BLASTn search, the closest match to the ITS sequence (
<accessionNumber box="[913,1041,410,437]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KX456184" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">KX456184</accessionNumber>
) of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hesler &amp; Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[1089,1221,410,437]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ulmicola">
<emphasis box="[1089,1221,410,437]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">C. ulmicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was 
<taxonomicName box="[1282,1451,410,437]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis box="[1282,1451,410,437]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">C. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<accessionNumber box="[144,274,446,473]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/OK376745" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">OK376745</accessionNumber>
), with 95% sequence similarity, which is consistent with the results of the phylogenetic analysis. 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">Crepidotus occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hesler &amp; Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[421,552,482,509]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ulmicola">
<emphasis box="[421,552,482,509]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">C. ulmicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in basidiospore size but differs in possessing clavate cheilocystidia and a much larger pileus (
<bibRefCitation author="Hesler, L. R. &amp; Smith, A. H." box="[289,534,518,545]" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" refId="ref7196" refString="Hesler, L. R. &amp; Smith, A. H. (1965) North American Species of Crepidotus. Hafner Publishing Company, New York, London, 168 pp." type="book" year="1965">Hesler &amp; Smith 1965</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
